description: 1. Neck: Take a measuring tape and measure around the neck (the circumference) where your dogs collar would sit. Make sure to take off his collar first. Write down this measurement in inches.  2. Girth: Measure your dog's circumference around the body from the top (between their shoulders) and around just behind the front legs. Be sure to keep the measuring tape snug to the body, especially on a fluffy breed, but bot squeezed too tight. Jot down this measurement in inches.  3. Length: Measure from the base of the neck on the back (where the collar sits) to the base of the tail and subtract 2 inches. Jot this down.
